						Thomas A. Flohn Sells 8,540 Shares of Lincoln Electric Holdings, Inc. (LECO) Stock					

June 1st, 2017  • 0 comments • Filed Under •
 by ABMN Staff



							Filed Under: Insider Trades • Market News 






Tweet










Lincoln Electric Holdings, Inc. (NASDAQ:LECO) SVP Thomas A. Flohn sold 8,540 shares of the stock in a transaction dated Thursday, June 1st. The stock was sold at an average price of $90.15, for a total transaction of $769,881.00. Following the transaction, the senior vice president now owns 31,160 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $2,809,074. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which is available through this hyperlink. 
Lincoln Electric Holdings, Inc. (LECO) traded up 2.69% during trading on Thursday, hitting $91.78. 416,082 shares of the stock were exchanged. The firm has a market cap of $6.04 billion, a PE ratio of 30.73 and a beta of 0.88. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $88.48 and its 200 day moving average is $83.71. Lincoln Electric Holdings, Inc. has a 52 week low of $56.02 and a 52 week high of $91.98. 


 Get Lincoln Electric Holdings Inc. alerts:



Lincoln Electric Holdings (NASDAQ:LECO) last posted its earnings results on Tuesday, April 18th. The industrial products company reported $0.88 EPS for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of $0.79 by $0.09. The company had revenue of $580.90 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $568.31 million. Lincoln Electric Holdings had a net margin of 8.50% and a return on equity of 26.69%. The firm’s revenue for the quarter was up 5.5% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period in the previous year, the firm posted $0.76 earnings per share.  Analysts expect that  Lincoln Electric Holdings, Inc. will post $3.67 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 





The firm also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Friday, July 14th. Stockholders of record on Friday, June 30th will be given a dividend of $0.35 per share. This represents a $1.40 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 1.53%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Wednesday, June 28th. Lincoln Electric Holdings’s payout ratio is presently 50.36%. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Thomas A. Flohn Sells 8,540 Shares of Lincoln Electric Holdings, Inc. (LECO) Stock” was originally  reported by American Banking News and is the sole property of of American Banking News. If you are reading this report on another publication, it was stolen and reposted in violation of United States and international copyright and trademark laws. The correct version of this report can be viewed at https://www.americanbankingnews.com/2017/06/01/thomas-a-flohn-sells-8540-shares-of-lincoln-electric-holdings-inc-leco-stock.html. 
A number of research firms have recently commented on LECO. Stifel Nicolaus  restated a “hold” rating and set a $88.00 price objective (up from $86.00) on shares of Lincoln Electric Holdings in a research note on Saturday, April 22nd. Barclays PLC  restated an “equal weight” rating and set a $82.00 price objective (up from $75.00) on shares of Lincoln Electric Holdings in a research note on Saturday, April 22nd. Royal Bank of Canada  restated a “hold” rating and set a $78.00 price objective on shares of Lincoln Electric Holdings in a research note on Monday, April 17th. Deutsche Bank AG reduced their price objective on shares of Lincoln Electric Holdings from $100.00 to $90.00 and set a “hold” rating for the company in a research note on Friday, April 28th. Finally, Zacks Investment Research upgraded shares of Lincoln Electric Holdings from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a research note on Wednesday, February 1st. Eight research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and three have assigned  a buy rating to the stock. The company presently has an average rating of “Hold” and a consensus target price of $80.43.
Several large investors have recently bought and sold shares of the company. Stellar Capital Management LLC acquired a new stake in  Lincoln Electric Holdings during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $2,121,000.  Dimensional Fund Advisors LP increased its stake in  Lincoln Electric Holdings by 1.9% in the fourth quarter. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 496,677 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $38,081,000 after buying an additional 9,410 shares during the last quarter.  Comerica Bank increased its stake in  Lincoln Electric Holdings by 3.6% in the fourth quarter. Comerica Bank now owns 47,211 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $3,830,000 after buying an additional 1,623 shares during the last quarter.  Cutter & CO Brokerage Inc. acquired a new stake in  Lincoln Electric Holdings during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $207,000.  Finally, Johnson Financial Group Inc. increased its stake in  Lincoln Electric Holdings by 157.1% in the fourth quarter. Johnson Financial Group Inc. now owns 2,250 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $173,000 after buying an additional 1,375 shares during the last quarter. 66.32% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 
Lincoln Electric Holdings Company Profile
Lincoln Electric Holdings, Inc is a manufacturer of welding, cutting and brazing products. The Company operates through three segments: Americas Welding, International Welding and The Harris Products Group. The Americas Welding segment includes welding operations in North and South America. The International Welding segment primarily includes welding operations in Europe, Africa, Asia and Australia.




